      "writtenOn": "2017-12-01T03:22:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is it valid to keep trying if this happens?\n\nBased on the implementation, the answer looks to be no. It’s important to document this because the implementation may also go berserk if it’s attempted again after returning kError. (In fact, you might want to provide a field to invalidate the object, and either test it when looking for the next note to fail fast with kError again, or just DCHECK it.",
      "revId": "83c3acca564849bab1705b4b2d39c9c6f53baeb9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
