      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-01T03:22:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don’t like leaving this exposed in the public interface. On the implementation side, it makes it too easy to accidentally return this. On the consumer side, you’d have to provide a bogus “case kRetry:” or “default:” to placate -Wswitch.",
      "revId": "83c3acca564849bab1705b4b2d39c9c6f53baeb9",
